WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.120
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

00:04.120 --> 00:05.170
Lonnie: The suspect goes by
the name of "Charlie,"

00:05.170 --> 00:06.380
no last name --
an obvious alias.

00:06.380 --> 00:08.920
He held a stash of
dozens of forged IDs,

00:08.920 --> 00:10.830
including one that
gained him access

00:10.830 --> 00:12.750
to the White House
in recent months.

00:12.750 --> 00:14.830
Secret Service
has been informed.

00:14.830 --> 00:16.670
His place of business
has been secured

00:16.670 --> 00:18.750
and protected as a crime scene.

00:18.750 --> 00:21.330
Agents conducted a thorough
search of the premises

00:21.330 --> 00:23.330
for other devices
that may have been used

00:23.330 --> 00:25.420
to infiltrate
Air Force Two's systems.

00:25.420 --> 00:28.330
There was a massive
stockpile of electronics

00:28.330 --> 00:30.500
that would've put RadioShack
to shame.

00:30.500 --> 00:33.290
The confiscated devices
are being decrypted.

00:33.290 --> 00:36.500
The suspect's associates were
briefly questioned and released,

00:36.500 --> 00:40.250
but Quinn Perkins and Associates
remains shut down

00:40.250 --> 00:41.250
until further notice.

00:41.250 --> 00:42.880
Is the suspect talking?

00:42.880 --> 00:44.580
The suspect
remains tight-lipped.

00:44.580 --> 00:45.750
I've got to hand it
to the man --

00:45.750 --> 00:49.000
he's been remarkably resistant
to our...

00:49.000 --> 00:50.500
methods of persuasion.

00:50.500 --> 00:51.830
[ Chains rattling ]

00:55.290 --> 00:56.880
[ Door slams ]

00:56.880 --> 00:59.040
[ Clears throat ]

00:59.040 --> 01:01.670
This can all stop,
Charlie.

01:01.670 --> 01:03.000
Are you kidding?

01:03.000 --> 01:04.670
I've never felt better.

01:04.670 --> 01:06.460
But you got to tell me,
though --

01:06.460 --> 01:07.960
are Bert and Ernie over there
Moroccan?

01:07.960 --> 01:10.540
'Cause I swear I had
the same full-body treatment

01:10.540 --> 01:11.710
at a hammam
in Marrakech.

01:11.710 --> 01:13.380
Are you ready to talk?

01:13.380 --> 01:15.290
I told you,
I'm being set up.

01:15.290 --> 01:16.750
I got nothing else to say.

01:16.750 --> 01:21.080
Sorry, when I said ready
to talk, I meant me to you.

01:21.080 --> 01:23.210
I have no interest
in keeping you here.

01:23.210 --> 01:25.120
Seeing you in pain
gives me no pleasure, truly.

01:25.120 --> 01:27.420
I'm just a guy
doing his job.

01:27.420 --> 01:30.920
And my job today is to get you
to walk out of here...

01:30.920 --> 01:33.540
without handcuffs.

01:33.540 --> 01:35.790
Oh, yeah?
How's that gonna happen?

01:35.790 --> 01:36.880
I offer you a deal.

01:36.880 --> 01:38.710
You sign, you go home --
simple as that.

01:38.710 --> 01:44.040
♪♪

01:44.040 --> 01:46.710
This is a con--
This is a confession.

01:46.710 --> 01:48.170
Filled with lies.

01:48.170 --> 01:50.750
We know that you were hired to
assassinate the Vice President.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.670
We're not after you.

01:52.670 --> 01:55.080
You sign this confession,
and you're on your merry way.

01:55.080 --> 01:57.080
We just need your signature,

01:57.080 --> 02:00.040
affirming the person who hired
you to kill Cyrus Beene was --

02:00.040 --> 02:02.380
Mellie Grant.

02:02.380 --> 02:08.000
♪♪

02:08.500 --> 02:10.330
Cyrus...

02:10.330 --> 02:12.170
Man, wow.

02:14.040 --> 02:16.380
You know, when that guy
goes for it, I mean...

02:16.380 --> 02:20.420
Hijacking his own plane,
framing the President...

02:20.420 --> 02:21.540
recruiting you.

02:21.540 --> 02:23.960
Is it crowded in there,
in his pocket?

02:23.960 --> 02:26.250
It's got to be jammed.

02:26.250 --> 02:29.460
You know,
your ability to concoct

02:29.460 --> 02:32.250
such a detailed conspiracy
was really admirable.

02:32.250 --> 02:33.540
But, unfortunately,

02:33.540 --> 02:35.420
you aren't gonna be able to
lie your way out of here.

02:35.420 --> 02:39.960
Your only ticket home
is punched with pen to paper.

02:39.960 --> 02:45.120
I won't be used by Cyrus
to impeach the President.

02:45.120 --> 02:46.290
I'm not a traitor.

02:46.290 --> 02:49.710
You'd be a patriot,
a liberator...

02:49.710 --> 02:50.960
and a free man.

02:53.500 --> 02:56.170
Once Cyrus Beene moves into
1600 Pennsylvania Avenue,

02:56.170 --> 02:58.670
you walk out this door,
fully pardoned.

02:58.670 --> 03:02.120
Sign the confession,
Charlie.

03:02.120 --> 03:07.790
♪♪

03:10.000 --> 03:11.210
Go to hell.

03:14.040 --> 03:15.540
He's all yours.

03:15.540 --> 03:20.250
♪♪

03:22.960 --> 03:25.880
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:32.960 --> 03:34.880
They took Charlie.
I know.

03:55.500 --> 03:57.920
[ Breathes shakily ]

03:57.920 --> 04:02.420
There are Feds at QPA.

04:02.420 --> 04:04.500
They've arrested Charlie,

04:04.500 --> 04:05.750
and now they're packing it
into boxes.

04:05.750 --> 04:07.250
Quinn, I'm so sorry --

04:07.250 --> 04:09.620
You know I don't give a damn
about Cyrus.

04:09.620 --> 04:13.210
I don't care if he staged
a hijacking for publicity.

04:13.210 --> 04:15.210
He wants the Oval.
And he can have it,
for all I care,

04:15.210 --> 04:16.620
but he can't
have Charlie.

04:16.620 --> 04:17.920
I understand.

04:20.330 --> 04:22.210
You shouldn't have
gone behind our backs.

04:22.210 --> 04:23.790
I didn't think
you would take the case

04:23.790 --> 04:25.210
if you knew it was for me.

04:25.210 --> 04:27.920
You're right --
we wouldn't have.

04:27.920 --> 04:30.920
But now it's not only for you
anymore, is it?

04:30.920 --> 04:33.460
What are you suggesting?

04:37.750 --> 04:39.330
[ Sighs ]

04:39.330 --> 04:41.170
A partnership.

04:41.170 --> 04:43.500
We have a common enemy,
and whatever our differences,

04:43.500 --> 04:45.830
right now,
we put them aside.

04:45.830 --> 04:49.250
Of course.
And, Liv, I want to
make something clear.

04:49.250 --> 04:52.040
I am doing this for Charlie,
not for you.

04:52.040 --> 04:53.670
Understand?

04:53.670 --> 04:55.120
I do.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.080
Then let's not waste
any more time.

05:00.420 --> 05:02.830
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

05:02.830 --> 05:04.880
Cyrus Beene
hijacked his own plane.

05:04.880 --> 05:06.120
And now
he's framing Charlie.

05:06.120 --> 05:08.040
Fitz: This is a new low,
even for Cyrus.

05:08.040 --> 05:11.000
We need to tell Mellie
that Cyrus is coming for her.

05:11.000 --> 05:12.500
And that Charlie's innocent.

05:12.500 --> 05:13.920
A President can fix that,
right?

05:13.920 --> 05:15.120
It's a hard sell,
politically.

05:15.120 --> 05:16.880
Not if we can prove that
the special prosecutor

05:16.880 --> 05:18.040
is in Cyrus's pocket.

05:18.040 --> 05:19.580
Is that what we think?

05:19.580 --> 05:21.170
Why is that
so hard to believe?

05:21.170 --> 05:23.380
Because it's Lonnie Mencken.
The man's record is impeccable.

05:23.380 --> 05:26.210
Cyrus hijacked a plane,
framed an ex-spy,

05:26.210 --> 05:27.670
and conflicted
an attorney general

05:27.670 --> 05:28.750
out of investigating him.

05:28.750 --> 05:30.000
Do you really think
he would leave

05:30.000 --> 05:31.620
the appointment of
special prosecutor to chance?

05:31.620 --> 05:33.580
Do you want to talk to Mellie
or should I?

05:33.580 --> 05:35.170
I want Charlie alive,
so not Liv.

05:37.210 --> 05:38.330
While you're
working on Mellie,

05:38.330 --> 05:39.960
the rest of us can
look into Lonnie,

05:39.960 --> 05:42.250
see if we can find anything
that pries him away from Cyrus.

05:42.250 --> 05:44.170
Whatever it takes
to bring Charlie home safely.

05:48.830 --> 05:51.420
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

05:51.420 --> 05:53.120
[ Sighs ]

06:01.460 --> 06:03.580
[ Lock beeps ]

06:08.920 --> 06:10.580
He didn't sign it?

06:10.580 --> 06:12.380
I'm afraid not.

06:12.380 --> 06:14.500
We knew he'd be
a tough nut to crack.

06:14.500 --> 06:15.670
These old spies,

06:15.670 --> 06:18.000
they'll never do anything
they don't want to do.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.040
All that
damn training.

06:20.040 --> 06:21.290
My men have training,
too.

06:21.290 --> 06:23.330
We need to be patient.

06:23.330 --> 06:25.670
Is there anything else?

06:31.120 --> 06:33.330
Wait.

06:35.040 --> 06:38.500
We're doing this wrong.

06:38.500 --> 06:42.210
It's not Charlie
we should be pressuring.

06:42.210 --> 06:44.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

06:58.500 --> 07:00.920
Hey.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.540
What're you doing?

07:02.540 --> 07:04.040
We'll be discussing
sensitive information.

07:04.040 --> 07:05.250
We need privacy.

07:05.250 --> 07:06.460
You can't be too careful

07:06.460 --> 07:08.120
when everyone has a phone
in their pocket.

07:13.750 --> 07:15.290
So you're back now?

07:16.880 --> 07:18.750
For this, I'm back.

07:18.750 --> 07:21.210
Okay.

07:25.580 --> 07:27.040
Are we ready?

07:31.500 --> 07:33.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
Abby: Alonzo Mencken, 64,

07:33.000 --> 07:35.420
former U.S. Attorney from the
Eastern District of Virginia.

07:35.420 --> 07:37.290
Recently appointed
Special Prosecutor

07:37.290 --> 07:38.790
in charge of the investigation

07:38.790 --> 07:41.120
into the hijacking
of Air Force Two.

07:41.120 --> 07:42.420
Ah.
You know what he looks like.

07:42.420 --> 07:44.500
Sorry. Couldn't find
any of your sticky paper.

07:44.500 --> 07:47.460
Lonnie graduated top of
his class from Stanford Law,

07:47.460 --> 07:49.460
where he met his wife.

07:49.460 --> 07:51.500
They've managed to stay together
all these years,

07:51.500 --> 07:53.460
for better or for worse --
and I mean worse.

07:53.460 --> 07:55.000
Uh, 20 years ago,
their only son, Adam,

07:55.000 --> 07:56.580
was gunned down in
a mass shooting at a mall.

07:56.580 --> 07:59.040
Adam was 9.
He died in Lonnie's arms.

07:59.040 --> 08:00.880
I remember this. It inspired him
to become a prosecutor.

08:00.880 --> 08:02.120
He's dedicated his life

08:02.120 --> 08:03.750
to keeping violent offenders
behind bars.

08:03.750 --> 08:04.830
All the while
earning a reputation

08:04.830 --> 08:06.670
for being tough but fair.

08:06.670 --> 08:08.880
I've protested a lot of
crooked prosecutors in my day

08:08.880 --> 08:10.120
but never Mencken.

08:10.120 --> 08:11.830
He's the epitome of
an honorable public servant.

08:11.830 --> 08:14.920
So how does someone like that
end up in Cyrus Beene's pocket?

08:14.920 --> 08:16.670
Money troubles, maybe?

08:16.670 --> 08:18.790
Has he recently received
a Cézanne-sized delivery?

08:18.790 --> 08:20.750
-Cézanne?
-We think Cyrus might've used

08:20.750 --> 08:23.330
the Cézanne Glackland
gave him to fund --

08:23.330 --> 08:24.920
We don't have
to recap right now.

08:24.920 --> 08:26.670
Does he have debts?
Is he a gambler?

08:26.670 --> 08:28.500
Has he made
any large purchases?

08:28.500 --> 08:30.380
Uh, he has a mortgage
and some credit-card debt --

08:30.380 --> 08:31.580
nothing out of the ordinary.

08:31.580 --> 08:33.330
No shady transactions,

08:33.330 --> 08:34.960
no secret
offshore bank accounts,

08:34.960 --> 08:36.330
no large deliveries
to his house.

08:36.330 --> 08:38.120
His web history
is Boresville, too --

08:38.120 --> 08:39.380
no weird porn sites,

08:39.380 --> 08:40.710
no late-night visits
to Craigslist.

08:40.710 --> 08:43.880
He even keeps his SafeSearch
on maximum setting.

08:43.880 --> 08:44.920
The guy is
a Goody Two-Shoes.

08:44.920 --> 08:46.670
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

08:46.670 --> 08:48.620
What?

08:50.210 --> 08:52.120
[ Sighs ]
Oh, damn it.

08:52.120 --> 08:53.540
Don't worry.
We'll keep at it --

08:53.540 --> 08:55.040
No, it's -- it's not that.
It's my nanny.

08:55.040 --> 08:56.380
Robin's ear infection
is flaring up.

08:56.380 --> 08:57.920
She's screaming
her little face off.

08:57.920 --> 08:59.620
Charlie was supposed to
pick up the prescription drops,

08:59.620 --> 09:01.790
but I guess
he didn't get the chance.

09:01.790 --> 09:03.710
Go.
Do what you have to do.

09:03.710 --> 09:09.290
♪♪

09:09.290 --> 09:10.290
[ Door opens ]

09:10.290 --> 09:15.620
♪♪

09:15.620 --> 09:21.210
♪♪

09:21.210 --> 09:23.170
Miss Perkins,
hope I'm not disturbing you.

09:30.880 --> 09:32.540
Let me
get this straight.

09:32.540 --> 09:34.500
You'd like Charlie to
sign a confession

09:34.500 --> 09:37.290
that would frame the President
of the United States

09:37.290 --> 09:39.710
for ordering him
to hijack Air Force Two,

09:39.710 --> 09:43.210
all in an effort to stage
some horrifically calculated

09:43.210 --> 09:44.750
assassination attempt
on you?

09:44.750 --> 09:46.380
More or less.

09:46.380 --> 09:49.210
[ Laughs ] Yeah,
there's no way in hell --

09:49.210 --> 09:50.830
It isn't really asking too much,
now, is it?

09:50.830 --> 09:52.540
Let Charlie go.

09:52.540 --> 09:55.120
You want to help your boyfriend,
then you need to help me.

09:55.120 --> 09:58.120
Convince Charlie to sign
the deal that's in front of him.

09:58.120 --> 10:00.120
Do it while the poor guy

10:00.120 --> 10:03.330
still has a hand left
to hold a pen, at least.

10:03.330 --> 10:05.880
Oh, this usually works for you,
right?

10:05.880 --> 10:08.080
Strong-arming loved ones into
doing things against their will.

10:08.080 --> 10:09.670
Not this time.
You want my help?

10:09.670 --> 10:12.500
I am not gonna help you --
-I'm assuming you voted for her.

10:12.500 --> 10:15.330
Had your cute little
"Future Is Female" T-shirt on

10:15.330 --> 10:17.170
when you went to the polls
that day,

10:17.170 --> 10:18.880
'cause, you know, girl power
and all that crap.

10:18.880 --> 10:20.460
You voted for Mellie Grant

10:20.460 --> 10:22.750
despite everything
you knew about her.

10:22.750 --> 10:24.330
You want to talk about
the things I know?

10:24.330 --> 10:25.670
Let's start with the things
I know about you.

10:25.670 --> 10:27.000
This isn't about me.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.580
I mean, it is,
at the end of day,

10:28.580 --> 10:29.670
but right here, right now,

10:29.670 --> 10:32.540
it's about your loving,
doting fiancé.

10:32.540 --> 10:36.040
You're choosing Mellie Grant
over the father of your child?

10:36.040 --> 10:38.420
This conversation's
over.

10:38.420 --> 10:41.080
What is it with you people
and Olivia Pope?!

10:41.080 --> 10:42.790
For the love of --

10:42.790 --> 10:44.710
It's like you're all
little wind-up toys,

10:44.710 --> 10:45.670
aimlessly fluttering about.

10:45.670 --> 10:47.170
After all this time?

10:47.170 --> 10:49.040
This has nothing to do with
Olivia Pope.

10:49.040 --> 10:51.120
Quinn, come on!

10:51.120 --> 10:54.170
Your intellect has always been
so remarkable.

10:54.170 --> 10:55.790
Olivia Pope still believes
she has a shot

10:55.790 --> 10:57.420
at getting back
to the White House.

10:57.420 --> 11:00.040
She needs Mellie Grant
to stay right where she is.

11:00.040 --> 11:02.380
She doesn't care about
poor Charlie.

11:02.380 --> 11:04.880
She's already
made her choice.

11:04.880 --> 11:06.710
Isn't it time
you made yours?

11:06.710 --> 11:12.330
♪♪

11:12.330 --> 11:13.710
The number
to a burner phone

11:13.710 --> 11:15.670
that I'll have in my possession
for 24 hours.

11:15.670 --> 11:17.830
If I don't hear from you,
well...

11:17.830 --> 11:20.880
my condolences to you
and your lovely family.

11:20.880 --> 11:26.500
♪♪

11:30.210 --> 11:31.920
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

11:34.040 --> 11:35.460
Where's Teddy?

11:35.460 --> 11:37.250
Geraldine's bringing him
in a couple of minutes.

11:37.250 --> 11:38.830
I was hoping we could
have a second to talk.

11:38.830 --> 11:41.290
Oh, I'm a little busy,
but...sure.

11:41.290 --> 11:42.460
Do you have another case

11:42.460 --> 11:44.120
you need the White House
involved in?

11:44.120 --> 11:46.380
I'm here to talk about
Charlie.

11:46.380 --> 11:48.580
[ Sighs ]
Here we go.

11:48.580 --> 11:50.080
He's innocent, Mellie.

11:50.080 --> 11:51.580
Let me guess --
Liv sent you.

11:51.580 --> 11:53.420
Nobody sent me.

11:53.420 --> 11:55.040
I'm here because
you need to know the truth.

11:55.040 --> 11:57.250
The man you have in custody
is innocent.

11:57.250 --> 11:59.420
He had nothing to do
with the hijacking.

11:59.420 --> 12:01.710
This is all Cyrus.

12:01.710 --> 12:02.920
Hoo-boy!

12:02.920 --> 12:04.500
This just keeps getting
better and better.

12:04.500 --> 12:06.460
Olivia is bored,
isn't she?

12:06.460 --> 12:08.250
No one wants to hire
the ousted Chief of Staff,

12:08.250 --> 12:10.790
so she's now
spinning delusional yarns

12:10.790 --> 12:13.710
about the Vice President
hijacking his own plane?

12:13.710 --> 12:15.000
He basically
admitted it to her.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.420
He planned the whole thing.

12:16.420 --> 12:17.960
For what reason?

12:17.960 --> 12:19.710
To give himself
a spotlight.

12:19.710 --> 12:21.330
He's gunning for your job,
Mel,

12:21.330 --> 12:23.540
and he's not waiting
till the end of your term.

12:23.540 --> 12:26.540
Gunning for my job
by almost crashing his plane?

12:26.540 --> 12:28.540
It doesn't make sense.

12:28.540 --> 12:30.920
[ Breathes deeply ]

12:30.920 --> 12:32.290
Do you have any evidence?

12:32.290 --> 12:34.540
[ Sighs ]

12:34.540 --> 12:36.170
No.

12:36.170 --> 12:38.380
Because you know
what makes sense?

12:38.380 --> 12:41.540
That Olivia paid Charlie,
her old buddy,

12:41.540 --> 12:44.420
and whoever else from that
gang of criminals she employs

12:44.420 --> 12:47.750
to help her plan
some elaborate coup,

12:47.750 --> 12:50.460
and now she's trying to cover it
up because Charlie got caught.

12:50.460 --> 12:53.960
Olivia has made
serious missteps.

12:53.960 --> 12:57.330
But she has always,
in her way,

12:57.330 --> 12:59.120
had your best interests
at heart --

12:59.120 --> 13:00.420
the country's
best interests.

13:00.420 --> 13:02.420
You know that.

13:02.420 --> 13:05.170
Cyrus has motive
to come after you,

13:05.170 --> 13:08.170
and there is no way
Olivia would go to this length

13:08.170 --> 13:10.670
to meddle with
your administration.

13:12.170 --> 13:14.420
[ Sighs ]

13:14.420 --> 13:17.420
Fitz, be careful...

13:17.420 --> 13:19.500
or you will end up
her accomplice.

13:22.080 --> 13:23.750
And I have
too much responsibility

13:23.750 --> 13:25.170
to be a single parent.

13:25.170 --> 13:28.290
[ Sighs ]

13:28.290 --> 13:30.960
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

13:30.960 --> 13:33.380
She won't hear it --
not from me, at least.

13:33.380 --> 13:35.000
She's got a lot of people
in her ear over there.

13:35.000 --> 13:36.710
Yeah --
Cyrus Beene and Jake.

13:36.710 --> 13:38.830
She'd rather trust them
than listen to reason,

13:38.830 --> 13:40.620
just because I...

13:40.620 --> 13:42.750
Because you lied to her.

13:42.750 --> 13:46.500
I don't blame her
for having her guard up.

13:46.500 --> 13:49.460
All I'm saying is,
we can't blame Mellie.

13:49.460 --> 13:50.790
We also can't give up on
getting through to her.

13:50.790 --> 13:52.080
We need her on our side.

13:52.080 --> 13:53.580
You have another idea?

13:53.580 --> 13:55.500
She'll take a meeting
with me.

13:55.500 --> 13:56.790
I might be able to
get through to her.

13:56.790 --> 13:58.290
Set something up.

14:05.460 --> 14:07.710
You okay?

14:07.710 --> 14:10.330
[ Chuckles ]

14:10.330 --> 14:12.960
You know you did
good work in there.

14:12.960 --> 14:15.620
In the White House.

14:15.620 --> 14:17.920
Just because
it ended badly --

14:17.920 --> 14:19.790
I know.

14:19.790 --> 14:21.830
We should
get back to work.

14:26.500 --> 14:28.210
Huck: No red flags
on Lonnie's wife's phone,

14:28.210 --> 14:29.500
and his brother's a dead end,
too.

14:29.500 --> 14:31.120
What if we look at it
from the other direction?

14:31.120 --> 14:32.880
The Cézanne is missing.
Cyrus didn't just

14:32.880 --> 14:35.210
stick a $100-million painting
in a closet.

14:35.210 --> 14:36.330
Abby:
The White House logs are clean.

14:36.330 --> 14:37.380
If he got
the painting out,

14:37.380 --> 14:38.710
it wasn't through
the front door.

14:38.710 --> 14:40.960
Could he have used
his assistant?

14:40.960 --> 14:42.290
Cyrus isn't that sloppy,
but --

14:42.290 --> 14:44.620
I'll check,
just in case.

14:44.620 --> 14:46.920
There you are.

14:46.920 --> 14:48.040
Hey.

14:48.040 --> 14:50.380
How's Robin?

14:50.380 --> 14:52.830
Fine.

14:52.830 --> 14:53.960
Everything okay?

15:00.420 --> 15:02.080
Quinn?

15:02.080 --> 15:05.790
They're offering Charlie
a deal.

15:05.790 --> 15:07.040
What kind of deal?

15:07.040 --> 15:08.960
Immunity, in exchange
for his cooperation.

15:08.960 --> 15:11.000
Cooperation? But he
didn't have anything to
do with the hijacking.

15:11.000 --> 15:13.540
I know.

15:13.540 --> 15:16.080
They want him to say
he did it for Mellie.

15:25.830 --> 15:27.120
Did you talk
to Lonnie Mencken?

15:27.120 --> 15:29.000
Who told you this?
-Cyrus.

15:29.000 --> 15:31.750
Cyrus had the nerve to
bring this to you directly?

15:31.750 --> 15:33.620
I'm in charge.

15:35.000 --> 15:40.670
♪♪

15:41.250 --> 15:42.080
You want him to
take the deal.

15:42.080 --> 15:43.710
-Wouldn't you?
-No.

15:43.710 --> 15:45.120
It saves Charlie's life.

15:45.120 --> 15:46.330
While ruining Mellie's.

15:46.330 --> 15:48.460
Ah.

15:48.460 --> 15:50.830
Well, at least we know
what your priorities are,

15:50.830 --> 15:52.040
not that I'm surprised.

15:52.040 --> 15:53.080
-That's not fair.
-Is it not?

15:53.080 --> 15:54.290
She's the President.

15:54.290 --> 15:56.040
Quinn, Liv,
clearly both of you are --

15:56.040 --> 15:57.620
She's your President.

15:57.620 --> 16:01.080
She's the trophy you won for
all your years of chasing power.

16:01.080 --> 16:02.920
Look -- even when
she's kicked you out,

16:02.920 --> 16:04.080
you won't let go of her.

16:04.080 --> 16:05.170
That's not
what this is about.

16:05.170 --> 16:07.250
If we don't fight
to stop this,

16:07.250 --> 16:09.040
we're responsible for
whatever comes next.

16:09.040 --> 16:10.880
Don't be so grandiose.

16:10.880 --> 16:12.710
You guys, can't we discuss this
a little bit more calmly?

16:12.710 --> 16:15.620
Quinn, this is about right
and wrong, about democracy --

16:15.620 --> 16:17.620
You lost your right
to give moral lectures

16:17.620 --> 16:19.170
when you ordered your father
to shoot me in a basement!

16:20.330 --> 16:22.620
[ Clears throat ]

16:22.620 --> 16:25.330
And it's not about
right and wrong, Olivia.

16:25.330 --> 16:26.710
And it's not about democracy.

16:26.710 --> 16:30.250
This is about family --
our family, not yours.

16:30.250 --> 16:35.880
♪♪

16:38.620 --> 16:44.250
♪♪

16:46.710 --> 16:55.080
♪♪

16:55.080 --> 17:03.330
♪♪

17:09.380 --> 17:10.620
Mr. Vice President,
are you happy

17:10.620 --> 17:11.880
a suspect has been
brought into custody?

17:11.880 --> 17:12.960
Man: Can you give us
any more details

17:12.960 --> 17:14.460
about the investigation?

17:14.460 --> 17:15.500
Would you like to
send a message to the suspect?

17:15.500 --> 17:16.790
Right now I'm putting
all my faith

17:16.790 --> 17:19.460
in Special Prosecutor
Mencken.

17:19.460 --> 17:22.250
I survived that hijacking
for a reason,

17:22.250 --> 17:23.670
and it's not to stand here

17:23.670 --> 17:26.250
and send vindictive messages
to the hijacker.

17:26.250 --> 17:30.880
I got a job to do, folks,
and I've got to get back to it.

17:30.880 --> 17:33.000
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

17:33.000 --> 17:34.710
[ Reporters all speaking ]
Thank you. We will.

17:34.710 --> 17:36.290
Next time we will.
Thank you.

17:36.290 --> 17:39.790
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

17:44.170 --> 17:48.120
Okay. Bye-bye.
Thank you.

17:48.120 --> 17:50.580
It's a possibility,
I suppose.

17:50.580 --> 17:52.540
But the -- the Vice President
masterminding

17:52.540 --> 17:55.330
a hijacking of his own plane
for...what?

17:55.330 --> 17:56.670
His turn
on the nightly shows?

17:56.670 --> 17:59.790
To start building his campaign.
To take over my job.

17:59.790 --> 18:01.750
Even for Cyrus,
it's a little...

18:01.750 --> 18:03.920
[ Sighs ]

18:03.920 --> 18:05.040
Do you have a reason
to suspect him?

18:07.580 --> 18:09.040
[ Sighs ]

18:11.210 --> 18:12.710
How did Olivia
get to you?

18:12.710 --> 18:15.620
I'm not saying that he's guilty,
but it's worth ruling out.

18:15.620 --> 18:17.880
And so it begins.

18:17.880 --> 18:21.210
Did you know that Cyrus told
a bunch of press this morning

18:21.210 --> 18:24.170
that he survived the hijacking
for a "reason"?

18:24.170 --> 18:26.540
Like he'd been anointed
or something.

18:26.540 --> 18:28.080
We were pushing him out.

18:28.080 --> 18:29.670
There's only one person
we pushed out,

18:29.670 --> 18:30.920
and now you're trying to
let her back in.

18:30.920 --> 18:32.040
Who's running this Oval?

18:32.040 --> 18:33.620
I am.

18:33.620 --> 18:35.750
And I want you to
look into Cyrus.

18:35.750 --> 18:36.750
Madam President --

18:36.750 --> 18:38.790
Jake.

18:38.790 --> 18:40.580
Do it.

18:48.580 --> 18:50.250
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

18:53.960 --> 18:55.500
Huck.

18:55.500 --> 18:57.460
I didn't know
you were in here.

18:57.460 --> 18:59.790
Is there
something you wanted?

18:59.790 --> 19:01.540
That woman
in the conference room.

19:01.540 --> 19:03.000
Was that Olivia?

19:11.040 --> 19:12.210
When you say
"Olivia"...?

19:12.210 --> 19:14.290
The old Olivia.

19:14.290 --> 19:15.920
From before
all the bad stuff happened.

19:15.920 --> 19:17.500
What do you think?

19:17.500 --> 19:20.170
I think
it looks like her.

19:20.170 --> 19:21.670
I think
it talks like her.

19:21.670 --> 19:23.540
But I don't trust myself

19:23.540 --> 19:26.750
because I know how badly
I want it to be true.

19:26.750 --> 19:29.580
And I might just be seeing
things that aren't really there.

19:32.000 --> 19:36.750
What do you see?

19:36.750 --> 19:38.460
I see the old Olivia,
too.

19:38.460 --> 19:41.670
Okay.

19:41.670 --> 19:43.000
Okay.

19:43.000 --> 19:45.290
Here's the thing, though.

19:45.290 --> 19:49.000
I want that Olivia back
as much as you do.

19:50.880 --> 19:52.960
So maybe we're both
seeing things.

19:52.960 --> 19:56.670
You feel like I do.

19:56.670 --> 19:59.210
I feel like you do.

20:01.830 --> 20:02.830
[ Knock on door ]

20:02.830 --> 20:04.580
Yes?

20:04.580 --> 20:05.710
Mr. Vice President,
do you have a moment?

20:05.710 --> 20:07.880
For you? Always.

20:07.880 --> 20:10.580
Something
on your mind?

20:10.580 --> 20:12.830
Well, I had a chat with
the Deputy Attorney General.

20:12.830 --> 20:14.380
-Did you?
-I did.

20:14.380 --> 20:16.290
He seems to be
under the impression

20:16.290 --> 20:18.710
that Lonnie Mencken found
his way onto the hijacking case

20:18.710 --> 20:20.670
based on
your recommendation.

20:20.670 --> 20:22.080
[ Chuckles ]

20:22.080 --> 20:24.330
[ Laughing ] Is --
Is that a fact?

20:24.330 --> 20:26.380
Well, I'm not sure.
That's why I'm here.

20:26.380 --> 20:31.330
Just happened to
run into the --

20:31.330 --> 20:33.210
the Deputy Attorney General,
did you?

20:33.210 --> 20:36.080
Or maybe
it wasn't happenstance?

20:36.080 --> 20:42.120
Maybe you reached out to him
because you heard a rumor.

20:42.120 --> 20:43.120
Yes?

20:45.620 --> 20:49.540
Well, Admiral,
let me assure you.

20:51.710 --> 20:53.670
Rumors are true.

20:53.670 --> 20:56.620
I confess.

20:56.620 --> 21:00.420
[ Chuckles ]
I hijacked my own plane.

21:06.580 --> 21:08.880
Well...

21:08.880 --> 21:11.880
I have to say this isn't how I
was expecting this to go at all.

21:11.880 --> 21:14.290
Tell you the truth,
me, either.

21:14.290 --> 21:16.920
But I'm sure you have
a pair of scissors

21:16.920 --> 21:19.000
or some other
lethal office supply

21:19.000 --> 21:20.920
hidden
in your jacket pocket

21:20.920 --> 21:24.710
that you planned to threaten me
with to get me to talk.

21:24.710 --> 21:26.080
So, let's skip that part,
shall we?

21:26.080 --> 21:27.380
It's boring
and a waste of time.

21:27.380 --> 21:29.500
Let's get right to
the good stuff.

21:29.500 --> 21:31.080
Which is...?

21:31.080 --> 21:33.920
The part where I tell you...

21:33.920 --> 21:35.670
that I have a plan --

21:35.670 --> 21:39.290
a plan that ends
with me planted firmly

21:39.290 --> 21:41.830
behind the desk
in the Oval Office.

21:41.830 --> 21:44.710
A plan that also includes
a job for you

21:44.710 --> 21:46.500
in the Beene administration.

21:46.500 --> 21:49.420
You think
I'm going to work for you?

21:49.420 --> 21:51.080
I think you're going to work
with me.

21:51.080 --> 21:53.500
If that's part
of your plan,

21:53.500 --> 21:55.790
I have to tell you
it's flawed.

21:55.790 --> 21:59.960
Ha, maybe, but...
I don't think so.

21:59.960 --> 22:02.620
You can refuse my offer,
but if you do,

22:02.620 --> 22:06.500
you will doom yourself to a life
as a second-class citizen.

22:06.500 --> 22:09.380
You can take me down,
cast me out, save the day.

22:09.380 --> 22:12.040
But you'll still never be
anything more to Mellie

22:12.040 --> 22:14.210
than a consolation prize --

22:14.210 --> 22:18.290
the thing she got
when she couldn't have Liv.

22:18.290 --> 22:21.380
Just like you were
Liv's consolation prize --

22:21.380 --> 22:26.210
the thing she got
when she couldn't have Fitz.

22:26.210 --> 22:28.420
Second place.

22:28.420 --> 22:31.000
Second choice.

22:33.620 --> 22:39.000
You're investigating me because
Liv put a bug in Mellie's ear.

22:39.000 --> 22:41.670
You out me?

22:41.670 --> 22:45.000
You prove Liv right.

22:45.000 --> 22:48.460
Their bond begins to mend,

22:48.460 --> 22:51.960
and it's only a matter of time
before they're a team again.

22:51.960 --> 22:54.290
Mellie gets
her first choice back.

22:54.290 --> 22:58.120
And if that happens,
you're out.

23:01.120 --> 23:02.500
I know
you don't like me.

23:02.500 --> 23:05.290
Hell,
I don't particularly like you.

23:05.290 --> 23:07.960
But I've seen the future,
Jake.

23:09.500 --> 23:11.330
It's us.

23:11.330 --> 23:13.080
Or it's them.

23:13.080 --> 23:15.710
Those are
the only options.

23:15.710 --> 23:18.170
You seem fairly certain
of that.

23:18.170 --> 23:19.670
I am.

23:19.670 --> 23:22.000
And you will be, too.

23:22.000 --> 23:27.620
Once you've really taken
some time to consider my offer.

23:27.620 --> 23:35.250
♪♪

23:35.250 --> 23:42.580
♪♪

23:42.580 --> 23:44.460
Admiral.

23:44.460 --> 23:47.210
Don't take too long
to make up your mind.

23:47.210 --> 23:51.290
This offer's only available,
as they say, for a limited time.

24:02.040 --> 24:03.960
[ Door opens ]

24:07.330 --> 24:09.170
Mr. Attorney General,
you wanted to see me?

24:09.170 --> 24:10.330
Yes.
Thought I'd check in on you,

24:10.330 --> 24:11.830
see how the investigation
is going.

24:11.830 --> 24:13.500
Please, have a seat.

24:13.500 --> 24:15.420
Well,
you know I can't discuss

24:15.420 --> 24:17.290
any of the details of
the investigation with you.

24:17.290 --> 24:19.170
Well, I was just wondering
if you needed a sounding board.

24:22.000 --> 24:23.960
I think
I'm gonna go now.

24:23.960 --> 24:26.170
Before I have to charge
the Attorney General

24:26.170 --> 24:28.210
of the United States
with obstruction of justice.

24:28.210 --> 24:31.250
The suspect you're questioning
down there is innocent.

24:31.250 --> 24:34.880
You know that.
-No. I don't know that.

24:34.880 --> 24:37.250
What I do know is that
that nameless thug

24:37.250 --> 24:39.790
worked on
Mellie Grant's campaign,

24:39.790 --> 24:42.620
for a firm founded by her former
chief of staff,

24:42.620 --> 24:44.580
a campaign that ended,
you may recall,

24:44.580 --> 24:45.920
with the assassination of

24:45.920 --> 24:47.620
Mellie Grant's
Democratic opponent

24:47.620 --> 24:49.750
and the wrongful arrest
of Cyrus Beene.

24:49.750 --> 24:51.380
Coincidence?

24:51.380 --> 24:53.170
Perhaps.

24:53.170 --> 24:55.500
But I can also put this
"Charlie" on the tarmac

24:55.500 --> 24:57.460
the day that Rashad
was assassinated.

24:57.460 --> 24:59.960
And I can link him
to the virus responsible for

24:59.960 --> 25:02.380
the attack on
Vice President Beene's plane.

25:02.380 --> 25:04.540
Frankly,
I've never prosecuted

25:04.540 --> 25:06.920
a more open-and-shut case
in my career.

25:06.920 --> 25:10.210
I stood in front of the American
people, and I vouched for you.

25:10.210 --> 25:11.710
You also told them
that you were

25:11.710 --> 25:13.830
recusing yourself
from this investigation.

25:13.830 --> 25:15.210
Why are you doing this?

25:15.210 --> 25:16.920
Does Cyrus
have something on you?

25:16.920 --> 25:18.750
Or are my friends right,
and you've suddenly developed

25:18.750 --> 25:20.540
an interest in
Post-Impressionist art?

25:20.540 --> 25:24.000
[ Sighs ]

25:24.000 --> 25:29.000
♪♪

25:29.000 --> 25:31.330
A very disturbed
young man --

25:31.330 --> 25:33.960
someone who shouldn't
even have been

25:33.960 --> 25:36.080
walking the streets
in the first place --

25:36.080 --> 25:39.710
once entered a superstore
and legally purchased

25:39.710 --> 25:42.460
half a dozen semiautomatic
killing machines.

25:42.460 --> 25:45.460
A week later,
I was with my boy in the mall.

25:45.460 --> 25:47.960
He was picking out presents
for his birthday.

25:47.960 --> 25:50.040
That same young man
was there.

25:51.580 --> 25:53.540
My boy was shot twice --

25:53.540 --> 25:55.250
once in the abdomen,

25:55.250 --> 25:57.790
once in the chest,
puncturing his lung.

25:57.790 --> 25:59.290
I told him he'd be okay,

25:59.290 --> 26:02.080
even as he was drowning
in his own blood.

26:02.080 --> 26:07.330
The very last words
I said to my son were a lie.

26:07.330 --> 26:09.210
Is that what this is about?
Adam?

26:14.000 --> 26:16.500
Mellie Grant may be
the most progressive Republican

26:16.500 --> 26:18.290
we've had in office
in a century.

26:18.290 --> 26:21.000
She's pro-choice,
pro-immigration,

26:21.000 --> 26:24.210
she got free college passed,
for crying out loud.

26:24.210 --> 26:28.920
But in one way,
she's exactly like the rest.

26:28.920 --> 26:31.790
Mellie loves her guns.

26:31.790 --> 26:38.670
♪♪

26:38.670 --> 26:45.580
♪♪

26:45.580 --> 26:52.790
♪♪

26:52.790 --> 26:54.710
Here we go again.

26:54.710 --> 26:57.170
You all are like a bunch of
door-to-door salesmen.

26:57.170 --> 26:58.420
You keep knocking,

26:58.420 --> 27:00.540
no matter how many times
I tell you I don't want any.

27:00.540 --> 27:03.420
But what if Liv is right
and Cyrus is coming after you?

27:03.420 --> 27:05.380
And what if there's a reason
why the people who

27:05.380 --> 27:07.750
care about you the most
are the ones who keep knocking?

27:14.960 --> 27:16.830
[ Sighs ]

27:16.830 --> 27:21.210
Unless I get hard evidence,

27:21.210 --> 27:25.250
there is no way that I am
buying in just on Olivia's word.

27:32.250 --> 27:34.960
Olivia isn't trying
to trick you.

27:34.960 --> 27:37.080
She's trying to save you.

27:37.080 --> 27:39.880
How can you trust her?

27:39.880 --> 27:41.830
Just like that?

27:41.830 --> 27:43.120
You remember
what she did to you?

27:43.120 --> 27:44.540
You mean
what she did to us?

27:46.750 --> 27:48.380
I remember.

27:48.380 --> 27:49.380
[ Scoffs ]

27:49.380 --> 27:51.000
Got me
the press secretary job

27:51.000 --> 27:52.790
so she could plant
in your head I was using you.

27:52.790 --> 27:55.170
Mm-hmm.

27:55.170 --> 27:57.460
But do you remember
why she did that?

27:57.460 --> 27:59.960
Because she's a condescending,
small person.

27:59.960 --> 28:02.170
A condescending,
small person

28:02.170 --> 28:03.460
who was trying to
make you president,

28:03.460 --> 28:05.620
who succeeded at
making you president,

28:05.620 --> 28:08.580
who right now is trying to
keep you president.

28:09.830 --> 28:15.790
She lied to my face
multiple times, Marcus.

28:15.790 --> 28:17.830
To my face.

28:17.830 --> 28:21.120
I know.

28:21.120 --> 28:23.170
But you also miss her,
don't you?

28:25.330 --> 28:27.750
[ Sighs ]

28:27.750 --> 28:30.540
This job -- It's...

28:34.120 --> 28:36.380
The fight is endless.

28:36.380 --> 28:38.710
And it's even harder

28:38.710 --> 28:40.500
if you don't have somebody
in your corner.

28:42.540 --> 28:44.210
I miss having her
in my corner.

28:44.210 --> 28:50.830
♪♪

28:50.830 --> 28:52.880
I miss her.

28:52.880 --> 28:55.330
I do.

28:55.330 --> 28:58.040
Olivia is still
in your corner.

28:58.040 --> 29:00.000
I know she is.
-Mm.

29:01.540 --> 29:03.040
And so am I.

29:05.790 --> 29:08.830
I will always be
in your corner.

29:08.830 --> 29:17.880
♪♪

29:17.880 --> 29:26.830
♪♪

29:26.830 --> 29:35.920
♪♪

29:40.580 --> 29:50.380
♪♪

29:50.380 --> 30:00.170
♪♪

30:00.170 --> 30:09.920
♪♪

30:09.920 --> 30:19.750
♪♪

30:19.750 --> 30:29.540
♪♪

30:29.540 --> 30:39.580
♪♪

30:39.580 --> 30:41.420
That doesn't belong to you
anymore.

30:41.420 --> 30:42.670
I know.

30:47.170 --> 30:48.880
Thank you
for meeting me.

31:01.460 --> 31:03.830
It's hard to look at,
isn't it?

31:03.830 --> 31:06.210
They really
trashed the place.

31:06.210 --> 31:08.170
They did.

31:08.170 --> 31:10.290
They don't care
about us.

31:10.290 --> 31:13.960
They were doing their jobs.
It isn't personal.

31:13.960 --> 31:16.420
That's exactly
what scares me.

31:16.420 --> 31:19.170
It's a machine --

31:19.170 --> 31:22.880
a giant meat grinder,
and Charlie's inside it.

31:22.880 --> 31:24.960
Can you blame me for
trying to pull him out?

31:24.960 --> 31:28.670
Of course not.
But...

31:28.670 --> 31:30.500
Never mind.

31:30.500 --> 31:32.580
We don't need to
go over it all again.

31:32.580 --> 31:35.290
Well, maybe we do.

31:35.290 --> 31:38.670
"If Quinn has to die
for the Republic,

31:38.670 --> 31:40.170
then she has to die."

31:42.250 --> 31:45.210
You said that.

31:45.210 --> 31:48.000
[ Sighs ]
[ Chuckling ] Republic.

31:48.000 --> 31:50.710
What is that, even?

31:50.710 --> 31:54.540
What ideal is so pure
that it can justify hundreds,

31:54.540 --> 31:57.170
thousands of people dying
to keep it intact?

31:57.170 --> 31:59.120
The United States
of America.

31:59.120 --> 32:00.790
A nation built on
the idea that

32:00.790 --> 32:02.710
its citizens
are its best stewards.

32:02.710 --> 32:04.750
Its citizens?

32:04.750 --> 32:06.880
Or its anointed band
of secret assassins?

32:06.880 --> 32:08.960
It doesn't mean I was right.
I was wrong.

32:08.960 --> 32:11.080
What happened that day...

32:11.080 --> 32:13.120
[ Sighs ]

32:18.000 --> 32:20.960
I tried to tell myself
it was for the Republic,

32:20.960 --> 32:23.540
but that was a lie.

32:23.540 --> 32:25.880
It was for me.

32:25.880 --> 32:27.920
For my own ambitions.

32:27.920 --> 32:30.540
I thought
I could fix the world

32:30.540 --> 32:33.250
with just a few
smart chess moves.

32:33.250 --> 32:35.040
I thought the ends
justified the means.

32:35.040 --> 32:37.500
But then you came along
talking about justice,

32:37.500 --> 32:39.120
and I was afraid
you would screw it all up.

32:39.120 --> 32:40.540
I would have
screwed it all up.

32:40.540 --> 32:42.040
You had every right to.

32:44.960 --> 32:49.120
I'm sorry, Quinn.

32:49.120 --> 32:54.580
Sorrier than
you can ever imagine.

32:54.670 --> 32:58.880
What it must feel like
for you now --

32:58.880 --> 33:01.040
for -- for me to stand there
and tell you

33:01.040 --> 33:05.500
that Charlie shouldn't take the
deal because of some principle.

33:05.500 --> 33:07.120
It's --
-I know it's wrong.

33:09.790 --> 33:11.500
[ Sighs ]

33:11.500 --> 33:14.620
Asking him to confess
to a crime he didn't commit,

33:14.620 --> 33:17.460
but we are not choosing between
right and wrong here, Liv.

33:17.460 --> 33:20.670
We're choosing between
being wrong and being dead.

33:20.670 --> 33:22.120
I know.

33:24.580 --> 33:27.750
[ Voice breaking]
My gut is telling me

33:27.750 --> 33:30.750
that we have to
protect Mellie.

33:30.750 --> 33:33.710
Letting her be
framed for treason?

33:33.710 --> 33:35.330
It's not right.

33:35.330 --> 33:38.460
The problem is
I don't trust my gut anymore.

33:38.460 --> 33:41.880
I, of all people,
have no right to tell you

33:41.880 --> 33:44.580
to stake Charlie's life
on an idea.

33:44.580 --> 33:46.040
The truth is I don't --

33:46.040 --> 33:48.540
I don't know anymore
what's right, what's wrong.

33:48.540 --> 33:51.830
What I do know...

33:51.830 --> 33:55.790
is I still trust you.

33:55.790 --> 33:59.380
Unlike me,
you never lost your way.

33:59.380 --> 34:03.170
That's why
I called you tonight.

34:03.170 --> 34:05.710
That's what I wanted
to say to you.

34:05.710 --> 34:09.790
Whatever you choose,

34:09.790 --> 34:11.710
I will support.

34:14.750 --> 34:17.420
It's your call, Quinn.

34:17.420 --> 34:19.460
It has to be.

34:19.460 --> 34:29.580
♪♪

34:29.580 --> 34:32.540
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

34:32.540 --> 34:33.960
Miss Perkins.

34:33.960 --> 34:37.290
I've given it
some thought.

34:37.290 --> 34:41.290
I can't tell Charlie
to sign that confession.

34:41.290 --> 34:43.920
It isn't right.

34:43.920 --> 34:45.120
How adorable.

34:45.120 --> 34:47.580
And how considerate of you
to call.

34:47.580 --> 34:50.330
Unfortunately for you,
I no longer need your help.

34:50.330 --> 34:53.460
What does that mean?

34:53.460 --> 34:55.500
It means I've made
alternate arrangements.

34:55.500 --> 34:57.540
Thank you for the call,
Miss Perkins.

34:57.540 --> 35:00.290
Enjoy the rest
of your evening.
Oh, oh, wait!

35:03.290 --> 35:05.250
Shall we?

35:16.620 --> 35:22.210
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:22.210 --> 35:24.790
It's about time you guys figured
out a way to get me out of here.

35:24.790 --> 35:26.460
[ Sighs ]

35:26.460 --> 35:30.210
I'm scared my money maker's
starting to look like a Picasso.

35:30.210 --> 35:31.960
Got a mirror?
Charlie.

35:31.960 --> 35:33.380
Toss me the keys
for these things, will you?

35:33.380 --> 35:36.040
I'm not here
to get you out.

35:40.500 --> 35:41.960
Not you, too.

35:41.960 --> 35:43.120
Jake.

35:43.120 --> 35:44.670
We need you to
take the deal.

35:44.670 --> 35:46.290
If you don't sign --

35:46.290 --> 35:47.500
What?

35:47.500 --> 35:49.380
You're gonna torture me?

35:49.380 --> 35:51.710
[ Sighs ]
Look at my face.

35:51.710 --> 35:53.880
Look at it.

35:53.880 --> 35:57.250
You think there's anything else
they could possibly do to me?

35:57.250 --> 35:59.330
Anything
you could do to me?

35:59.330 --> 36:00.790
Not to you.

36:03.120 --> 36:05.420
My assignment is to make you
sign the confession.

36:05.420 --> 36:07.540
By any means necessary.

36:09.830 --> 36:11.960
Don't you go
anywhere near her!

36:11.960 --> 36:13.250
No, unh-unh!

36:13.250 --> 36:14.380
You do not
get to do that.

36:14.380 --> 36:16.620
How dare you try to
put this on me?

36:16.620 --> 36:19.000
You think
I want to kill Quinn?

36:19.000 --> 36:20.330
I like Quinn.

36:20.330 --> 36:22.250
Hell, even you're on
my nice list these days,

36:22.250 --> 36:24.330
present circumstances
excluded.

36:24.330 --> 36:26.290
The last thing I want to do is
make your baby girl an orphan.

36:26.290 --> 36:28.380
But Cyrus made his call
to the bullpen,

36:28.380 --> 36:30.790
and he brought in
his closer.

36:30.790 --> 36:32.460
So now I'm here to close.

36:32.460 --> 36:34.830
I can't just take down
the president like that.

36:34.830 --> 36:36.750
You can.
And you will.

36:36.750 --> 36:38.500
You know how I know that?

36:38.500 --> 36:40.620
Because
I was at the funeral.

36:40.620 --> 36:42.540
I stood next to you
the first time you buried Quinn,

36:42.540 --> 36:44.750
shooting those bullets
into the ground.

36:44.750 --> 36:48.460
I saw how much loved her,
how much you needed her.

36:48.460 --> 36:51.080
It's the reason why rule number
one is rule number one.

36:51.080 --> 36:52.620
I said it to Quinn, myself,

36:52.620 --> 36:55.460
the day I welcomed her
into B613 -- no family.

36:55.460 --> 36:59.210
When you break rule number one,
you lose control.

36:59.210 --> 37:01.380
And when you lose control,
someone else takes it.

37:01.380 --> 37:04.080
I took it.

37:06.170 --> 37:07.210
I am in control.

37:10.620 --> 37:13.170
I'm not asking you to
sign the confession, Charlie.

37:13.170 --> 37:15.790
You have no choice,
no control.

37:15.790 --> 37:18.750
You will sign it.

37:18.750 --> 37:20.880
'Cause if you don't,

37:20.880 --> 37:22.420
you won't have control of

37:22.420 --> 37:24.380
when Quinn actually
goes in the ground.

37:27.580 --> 37:28.880
But I will.

37:28.880 --> 37:36.250
♪♪

37:36.250 --> 37:38.330
[ Sighs ]

37:38.330 --> 37:43.500
♪♪

37:43.500 --> 37:45.420
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

37:48.500 --> 37:50.750
Hmm.

37:50.750 --> 37:52.330
Mm.

37:52.330 --> 37:56.540
Hmm.

37:56.540 --> 37:59.170
Hmm.

38:06.790 --> 38:09.580
Good morning,
Mr. Walker.

38:09.580 --> 38:12.040
Hmm.
-Good morning, Ms. President.

38:12.040 --> 38:13.580
[ Chuckles ]

38:13.580 --> 38:15.460
[ Chuckles ]

38:15.460 --> 38:16.790
I prefer Madam.

38:16.790 --> 38:18.170
Hmm.
-Mm.

38:18.170 --> 38:20.540
[ Knock on door ]

38:20.540 --> 38:21.580
[ Gasps ]

38:21.580 --> 38:23.120
Oh! Um, Madam President.

38:25.460 --> 38:28.290
Rachel, what is it?
[ Sighs ]

38:31.710 --> 38:33.040
Madam President.

38:35.670 --> 38:37.500
Lonnie Mencken just served me
with a subpoena.

38:37.500 --> 38:39.420
A subpoena.
For me.

38:39.420 --> 38:43.170
Because apparently,
Charlie is saying I hired him!

38:43.170 --> 38:45.330
A person with no last name

38:45.330 --> 38:47.880
is accusing me
of hijacking that plane,

38:47.880 --> 38:50.120
and people are actually
believing him.

38:50.120 --> 38:51.540
There is something very,
very wrong here,

38:51.540 --> 38:54.620
something very,
very Cyrus Beene.

38:54.620 --> 38:57.580
We need to handle this
immediately.

38:57.580 --> 38:59.710
Get rid of the special
prosecutor, bury the subpoena --

38:59.710 --> 39:01.580
I don't think
that's wise.

39:01.580 --> 39:03.420
Jake,
are you hearing me?

39:03.420 --> 39:07.580
The President of the
United States has been served.

39:07.580 --> 39:09.380
The press will be on this
any minute,

39:09.380 --> 39:12.960
and when they are,
stock markets crash, polls sink.

39:12.960 --> 39:14.670
This administration
is going down.

39:14.670 --> 39:16.880
No, Madam President.

39:16.880 --> 39:19.330
You're going down.

39:19.330 --> 39:21.750
B613 no longer serves you,

39:21.750 --> 39:23.580
and I don't think it's wise

39:23.580 --> 39:25.290
to take on the special
prosecutor without it.

39:25.290 --> 39:27.420
But you and Olivia
can take your chances.

39:29.880 --> 39:32.120
Olivia was right.

39:35.670 --> 39:40.040
She was right about the whole
thing, and you were wrong.

39:40.040 --> 39:42.210
I'm sorry,
did you get your feelings hurt

39:42.210 --> 39:44.000
because a woman did the job
better than you did,

39:44.000 --> 39:46.830
or is this because I didn't want
to hold hands in the Oval?

39:46.830 --> 39:48.540
I need you right now!

39:48.540 --> 39:50.540
I tried to be
an adviser to you,

39:50.540 --> 39:53.210
to give you my loyalty,
but you didn't want that.

39:55.080 --> 39:56.750
Good luck to you.

39:58.670 --> 39:59.830
Jake!

40:01.670 --> 40:03.710
[ Door closes ]

40:03.710 --> 40:06.540
Earth-shattering news out of
the Justice Department today.

40:06.540 --> 40:08.420
Sources there report
that Lonnie Mencken,

40:08.420 --> 40:11.000
the special prosecutor
leading the investigation

40:11.000 --> 40:13.120
of the hijacking
of Air Force Two,

40:13.120 --> 40:15.670
has issued a subpoena
to President Grant.

40:15.670 --> 40:17.790
No comment from the White House
at this time,

40:17.790 --> 40:20.670
but the swiftness of this
action has many wondering

40:20.670 --> 40:22.670
what information
Mencken may have uncovered

40:22.670 --> 40:24.920
from the suspect
arrested earlier this week

40:24.920 --> 40:26.960
and what role
the president herself

40:26.960 --> 40:29.420
may have played
in the hijacking.

40:29.420 --> 40:31.540
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

40:33.120 --> 40:35.000
[ Sighs ]

40:42.210 --> 40:43.750
You okay?

40:59.290 --> 41:01.830
I'm sorry, Huck.

41:01.830 --> 41:04.210
We haven't lost yet.

41:04.210 --> 41:07.250
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm not talking about that.

41:09.330 --> 41:10.790
That was the old Liv.

41:10.790 --> 41:13.790
The one who did
all those things.

41:13.790 --> 41:16.500
She's gone now.

41:16.500 --> 41:18.080
Right?

41:18.080 --> 41:20.210
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

41:30.710 --> 41:31.880
I have to go.

41:31.880 --> 41:34.460
[ Footsteps echoing ]

41:37.460 --> 41:39.210
Wait.

41:39.210 --> 41:41.330
We've all done
bad things.

41:41.330 --> 41:43.620
We've all hurt people.

41:43.620 --> 41:50.000
♪♪

41:50.000 --> 41:56.620
♪♪

41:56.620 --> 41:58.380
I need you to
do something for me.

41:58.380 --> 42:04.420
It's what you do next
that matters.

42:08.710 --> 42:09.880
Be my Command again.

42:09.880 --> 42:17.290
♪♪

42:17.290 --> 42:19.120
Kill Cyrus Beene.

42:19.120 --> 42:24.920
♪♪

42:29.120 --> 42:38.460
♪♪

42:38.460 --> 42:48.080
♪♪

42:48.080 --> 42:57.420
♪♪
